Defines a simple OLAP Result and Metadata.

<h2>Overview</h2>

The OlapModel provides access to the {@@link com.tonbeller.jpivot.olap.model.Result}
of a query. It does not specify the query itself (e.g. what data will be displayed).
<p>

The interfaces in this package define a minimal OLAP result. The
definitions are independent of an implementation like
<a href="http://mondrian.sourceforge.net">Mondrian</a> or
JOLAP. It only defines what is necessary to display the result to the user.

<h2>OLAP Result</h2>

<img src="doc-files/result.gif">

<p>

To support "ragged hierarchies" or "parent-child hierarchies" no 
assuptions are made regarding the number, ordering or hierarchy of Levels 
instances.

See 
Microsofts definition of <a href="http://www.ddart.net/mssql/sql2000/html/olapdmad/agdimensions_5ab7.htm">Parent-Child Hierarchy</a>

